4 HJR___ SUPPORTING ADDITIONAL FUNDING FOR CAREER AND
5 TECHNICAL EDUCATION.
6
7 WHEREAS, Career and Technical Education (CTE) is an
8 educational approach that provides students with skills,
9 knowledge, and experiences necessary to enter the labor
10 market typically delivered through career-related courses;
11 and
12 WHEREAS, according to the Association for Career and
13 Technical Education, 34 percent of Alabama jobs will require
14 education beyond high school but less than a bachelor's
15 degree by 2031; and
16 WHEREAS, CTE programs prepare students for these jobs
17 in key Alabama industries such as agriculture technology and
18 food products, bioscience, metals and advance materials, and
19 operations and logistics; and
20 WHEREAS, in a concerted effort to support CTE in
21 Alabama, the Legislature enacted Act 2025-269 appropriating
22 $100,000,000 from the Education Trust Fund Advancement and
23 Technology Fund to the State Department of Education to
24 provide matching grants to local education agencies to
25 develop regional career technology centers throughout the
26 state, including capital outlay and equipment; now
27 therefore,
Page 1

therefore,
HJR189 INTRODUCED
28 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
29 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That we encourage and support an
30 additional $150,000,000 appropriation by the Legislature in
31 the 2026 Regular Session to continue to support and expand
32 CTE in Alabama.
